text.tspan: Quantity of a commodity available for use within a country after accounting for trade and stock changes. It is
calculated as production plus imports, minus exports, and adjusted for changes in stocks. Nuts is the sum of all
nut crops including brazil nuts, cashews, almonds, walnuts, pistachios, and areca nuts.
Data source: Food and Agriculture Organization of the United Nations (2024)
Note: FAOSTAT applies a methodological change from the year 2010 onwards.
